      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Thinking You Can Renew</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">The Croatia DN visa is NOT renewable. After 12 months, you must leave for 6 months before reapplying. Plan accordingly.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Insufficient Insurance</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">Travel insurance or basic nomad plans may not meet Schengen standards. Ensure €30,000+ coverage with repatriation included.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Missing Police Registration</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">You must register with local police within 3 days of arrival. Hotels do this automatically; for apartments, ensure your landlord handles it or go yourself.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Working with Croatian Clients</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">The DN visa only covers remote work for foreign employers. Taking Croatian clients requires a different work permit.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Summer Accommodation Prices</h3>
