  <!-- Section: FAQ -->
  <section id="faq" class="scroll-mt-24 mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Can I really not renew the visa?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">
          Correct. The Croatia DN visa is capped at 12 months and cannot be renewed. After your year ends, you must leave and wait 6 months before applying again. This is a significant limitation compared to other countries.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Do I pay Croatian taxes?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">
          No. Digital nomads on this visa are explicitly exempt from Croatian income tax on foreign earnings. You may still have tax obligations in your home country.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Can I travel in the Schengen Area?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">
          Yes. Since Croatia joined Schengen in 2023, your residence permit allows travel throughout the 27-country Schengen zone. This is a major benefit for European exploration.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">What about the seasons?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">
          Coastal Croatia is seasonal. Summers (June-August) are crowded and expensive. Shoulder seasons (April-May, September-October) offer best value. Winters are quiet with some closures. Zagreb is consistent year-round.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is the internet reliable?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">
          Yes, generally. Zagreb has excellent fiber coverage. Coastal cities have good infrastructure in tourist areas. Remote islands may have spotty connectivity. Always test before committing to long-term housing.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Can I bring my family?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">
          Yes, dependents can accompany you. Spouses may apply separately if they meet income requirements. Children can be included in your application. Budget for additional insurance costs.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

